{"key":"processedPost-13534452","value":{"id":13534452,"first":13533905,"last":13536875,"when":1290617536,"utime":"11/24/10 06:52 PM","content":"Low level ambient light will stimulate slightly faster colonization because mycelium derives energy from light.&nbsp; There is evidence that very bright light, such as used for pinning will actually slow down colonization.&nbsp; However, normal ambient room light from day one is actually a good thing.&nbsp; Just don't put your colonizing spawn in front of a window in direct sunlight.&nbsp; The old advice to 'colonize in total darkness' is bogus and has been proved incorrect over many tens of thousands of grows.<br />RR","title":"Re: incubation with light"}}